  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Denmark&#x2019;s contribution to the Special Fund of the Optional Protocol to the Convention against Torture (OPCAT) 2020 -2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Special Fund for OPCAT is a unique mechanism of torture prevention and the only operational fund established by an international human rights treaty. Its support to national preventive mechanisms, the establishment of which is a core obligation under the Optional Protocol to the Convention against Torture is key in preventing torture at the national level. 

The main objective of the development cooperation is effective prevention of torture through supporting projects contributing to the establishment or strengthening of NPMs in developing countries, including Benin, Mauritania, Mali, Niger, Senegal and Togo, in accordance with OPCAT and recommendations of the SPT or through the support of their education programmes.</narrative>
  </description>
